description:
persona.rs update() issues up to 4 separate round-trip UPDATE queries (lines 85-111), one per field. Each field check is an independent conditional send to SQLite.

Fix: build a SET clause dynamically and send one UPDATE. Standard pattern:

    let mut sets = vec![];
    let mut binds = vec![];
    if let Some(v) = display_name { sets.push("display_name = ?"); binds.push(v); }
    // ... etc.
    if sets.is_empty() { bail!(...); }
    let sql = format!("UPDATE personas SET {} WHERE username = ?", sets.join(", "));

This is not about performance (CLI command, single call) — the issue is that if two of the four queries succeed and the third fails, the persona is left in a half-updated state with no indication to the user. The transaction semantics are wrong.
